 that\nthe new algorithm is suitable for implementation on massively parallel\ndistributed memory supercomputers, showing two numerical examples run with more\nthan one billion degrees of freedom in space. To our knowledge, at present\nthese are the largest simulations ever run with unstructured WENO finite volume\nschemes.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Thu, 29 Dec 2016 22:31:50 GMT"}],"update_date":"2018-04-18"}
