thermore,\nMg- and Fe-rich aqueously altered minerals are dominant at different phases of\nthe alteration process. Thus, the contrasting spectral slope evolution between\nthe Fe- and Mg-rich samples in these experiments may indicate that space\nweathering trends of volatile-rich asteroids have a compositional dependency\nthat could be used to determine the aqueous histories of asteroid parent\nbodies.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Fri, 30 Dec 2016 06:00:15 GMT"}],"update_date":"2017-01-02"}
